texts: Pia Ranada talks about the ban against coverage, the string of threats, and the lonely business of reporting on the President. READ: Reporter Pia Ranada: 'If I can be targeted, so can any one else who is critical'

Reporters Pia Ranada, Mara Cepeda, Camille Elemia, Ralf Rivas and correspondents Bobby Lagsa and Raymon Dullana file a petition at the Supreme Court to lift the ban on Rappler’s coverage of President Rodrigo Duterte on April 11, 2019. Photos by LeAnne Jazul/Rappler
JUST IN. Pres Duterte designates Vice President Leni Robredo as the Co-Chairperson of the Inter-Agency Committee on Anti-Illegal Drugs (ICAD). | via @piaranada
President Duterte certifies as urgent Senate Bill No 1219, which focuses on salary increase for government employees, grant of additional benefits. | via @piaranada
